    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCan nvim support setting the position of the symbol in the sign colnum, as shown in the following figure?\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/eda735f7-d43f-4cec-970c-c44b3d5c27c9)\r\nI want to set a certain sign to appear in a fixed sign colnum. I learned that sign_place() doesn't seem to be able to do this.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe sign appears in the fixed sign colnum.",
