        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "In the previous discussion( [#19719](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/19719) and [#19737](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/19737) ), I saw that it is now possible to reuse the same column by setting the priority of the same type of mark, this helps more important symbols stand out on the far left, as shown in the figure below:\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b98b5b72-1d85-4e47-a54d-ce714e4dfc58)\r\n\r\nBut in a column of flags with the same priority (No higher priority flag exists), the flags are drawn from left to right, which results in the following situation(red Marking):\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f34f0a30-470c-4f6f-946e-2c64fdb81c53)\r\n\r\nThe 'x' sign is displayed on the far left, which is not aligned with the 'x' sign above, which looks very confusing. In fact, I have also seen similar discussions here: [#10106]ï¼Œbut there seems to be no valid conclusion(https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/10106)\r\n\r\nIf logos of the same type can be aligned in the same column, it will enhance the visual experience, so I am looking forward to this feature being supported, thanks!",
